<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1952-02-01T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1950-12-31T12:00:00-05:00" n="217" subtype="editorial-note" type="document" xml:id="d217">
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">No. 682</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">Editorial Note</hi>
                            </head>
                            <p>On June 2, the Department of State announced that because of
                                conditions currently existing in Czechoslovakia, American passports
                                    <pb facs="0403" n="1369" xml:id="pg_1369"/> of private travelers
                                were no longer valid to proceed to that country. For the text of the
                                brief Department statement to the press, see Department of State <hi rend="italic">Bulletin</hi>, June 11, 1951, page 932.</p>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>